               <msContents>
                  <summary>An incomplete abridgement of the <title>Dah Majlis</title> (Ten Assemblies) in alternating prose and verse, anonymously redacted from the <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Rawz̤at al-Shuhadā’  
                  </title> (Garden of Martyrs) of <persName role="ant" change="#role-assignment" key="person_90770167" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90770167/" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" >Ḥusayn Vāʻiẓ Kāshifī, (d. ca. 1504)</persName> related biographcial accounts of the family of the Prophet that especially highlights afflictions endured by Ḥusayn bin ‘Alī and those loyal to him at the Battle of Karbala. 
                     The volume lacks a title and preface and opens abruptly with the first Majlis on <locus from="1a" to="1a">1a</locus> and then continues with not just ten, but fourteen <hi rend="italic">majālis</hi>. 
                     Although undated, the colophon indicates that a scribe named <persName xml:lang="fa" type="supplied" key="person_f3838" role="scr" change="#role-assignment">Sharaf ‘Alī</persName> copied the manuscript on behalf of <persName xml:lang="fa" type="supplied" key="person_f2234" role="scr" change="#role-assignment">Mirzā Bahā’ al-Dīn ‘Alī Bayg</persName>, proabbly in circa <date cert="medium" calendar="#Gregorian" when="1700">1700 CE</date>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_146-item1">
                     <author role="ant" change="#role-assignment" key="person_90770167" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90770167/"><persName  xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" >Kāshifī, Ḥusayn Vāʻiẓ, d. 1504 or 5<lb/> <foreign xml:lang="fa">حسين واعظ كاشفى</foreign>
                     </persName></author>
                     <editor key="person_f3838" role="scr" change="#role-assignment"><persName xml:lang="fa">Sharaf ‘Alī</persName></editor>
                     <editor role="pat" change="#role-assignment" key="person_f2234"><persName xml:lang="fa">Mirzā Bahā’ al-Dīn ‘Alī Bayg</persName></editor>
                     <author role="abr" key="person_f407">Anonymous</author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6745">Dah Majlis</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_6745">ده مجلس</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_6745">Dah Majālis</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" type="alt" key="work_6745">ده مجالس</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="beginning">
                        <locus from="1a" to="1a"> برگ ۱ر (folio 1a):</locus>
                        مجلس اول در بیان کیفیت وقوع مصیبت کبری و واقعۀ عظمی وفات سید انبیا محمد مصطفی صلی الله علیه و آله از ابن عباس مرویست که چون حضرت رسول صلی الله علیه و آله از حجة الوداع برگشت بآنحضرت معلوم شد که رحلت او بعالم قدس نزدیک شده…</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"></explicit>
                     <colophon>Completed by <persName xml:lang="fa" type="supplied" key="person_f3838" role="scr" change="#role-assignment">Sharaf ‘Alī</persName> on behalf of<persName xml:lang="fa" type="supplied" key="person_f2234" role="pat" change="#role-assignment">Mirzā Bahā’ al-Dīn ‘Alī Bayg</persName>.</colophon>
                     <note>For a copy of the full work by Kāshifī, see Rylands <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6874"><idno>Persian MS 376</idno></ref></note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <!-- Double-check after imaging, as some of these may actually be subtopics, given only 14 Majlis -->
